Literature Review
Research Question #1: Academic Stressors
As school life becomes more competitive and burdensome, stress has become a common
term for everyday life among students in India (Kumar & Talwar, 2014). Characterized by
various symptoms in the form of stress reactions, it has become a significant cause for various
psychological and behavioral problems in Indian school students (Arun & Chavan, 2009; Deb et
al., 2015; Kumar & Talwar, 2014; Mathew et al., 2015; Parikh et al., 2019; Verma et al., 2002).
Parikh et al. (2019) state that studies conducted among school-going adolescents in urban India
indicate that at least one in five adolescents endures high-stress levels in their daily lives. These
statistics are bolstered by the research conducted by Deb et al. (2015), which reports that 63.5%
of higher secondary students in Kolkata experience academic stress. These academic anxieties
may appear from various sources in a student's ecological environment, including stress from
family, peers, schools, communities, and various other sources (Parikh et al., 2019). This
literature review will investigate the various stressors faced by Indian school students concerning
these factors.
